{# Persistent form-error summary (LRA-158, WCAG 2.2 SC 4.1.3).

   Rendered unconditionally so the role="alert" region is always present in the
   DOM: a 422 re-render then fills an existing live region rather than inserting
   a brand-new node, which assistive tech announces more reliably. When the form
   is valid the region is sr-only and empty, so it occupies no space and stays
   silent. A single source of truth for the dialog/card form error block, so
   callers no longer hand-roll the alert markup.

   @param form    The Symfony form view.
   @param ?string testid  Optional data-testid (defaults to "form-error"). #}
{% set testid = testid|default('form-error') %}
<div
    role="alert"
    data-testid="{{ testid }}"
    class="{{ form.vars.errors|length > 0 ? 'mb-4 rounded-md border border-danger/30 bg-danger/10 p-3 text-sm font-semibold text-danger' : 'sr-only' }}"
>
    {%- if form.vars.errors|length > 0 -%}
        {{ form_errors(form) }}
    {%- endif -%}
</div>
